F velocity to increase for strongly decaying sunspots, whereas the changing EF velocity has no impact on the MF.{\{}$\backslash$textless{\}}i{\{}$\backslash$textgreater{\}}Conclusions. {\{}$\backslash$textless{\}}i/{\{}$\backslash$textgreater{\}}On 3 h averages, the EF velocity scales with the size of sunspots, while the MF properties show no significant correlation with the EF or with the sunspot size. This we interpret as a hint that the physical origins of EF and MF are distinct.},
